The AEneid consists of twelve books and embraces a period of eight years. In the first book AEneas is driven by a storm to the coast of Africa, where he is received by Dido, queen of Carthage. In the second and third books AEneas tells Dido the sad story of the fall of Troy and of his own escape, and recounts the many dangcrs of the voyage from Troy to Drepanum in Sicily, where he buried his father.
